hands_on_practices.problem:
Consider the function $f$ defined on the interval $[0, 1]$ by
$$
f(x) = \begin{cases}
5 & \text{if } x = \frac{1}{2} \\
2 & \text{if } x \in [0, 1] \setminus \{\frac{1}{2}\}
\end{cases}
$$
Let $P = \{x_0, x_1, \dots, x_n\}$ be any arbitrary partition of the interval $[0, 1]$, where $0 = x_0 < x_1 < \dots < x_n = 1$. The lower Darboux sum of $f$ with respect to the partition $P$ is denoted by $L(f, P)$.

Determine the value of the lower Darboux sum $L(f, P)$. Your answer should be a single numerical value.
